article.headline: New Hampshire 71, Hartford 57
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Chris Vetrano scored a career-high 19 points and had four assists Thursday night to lead New Hampshire to a 71-57 victory over Hartford. UNH (8-18 overall, 4-11 America East), led the entire game, by as many as 15 points with 4:59 remaining in the half, when it was up 36-22 Hartford (7-17 overall, 3-12 America East) managed to cut the UNH lead to eight points with 4:43 to play. However, UNH responded with an 8-0 run to make it 68-52 with 2:05 left on the clock. UNH's Ben Sturgill contributed 15 points while Mike Christensen had 13. Craig Walls contributed a career-high 14 rebounds. Hartford was led by the 17-point scoring of Aaron Cook, the only Hawk to score in double figures. Sean Regan contributed 10 rebounds.
